entry.lex: Alan Shepard was born in New Hampshire and died in California. He was a crew member of Apollo 14 which is operated by NASA. He was awarded the Distinguished Service Medal in the US Navy, which is higher than the Dept of Commerce Gold Medal.

entry.lex: Apollo 12 was operated by NASA. It had many crew members, including: its backup pilot, Alfred Worden; its crew member Alan Bean (Alan LaVern Bean, retired June 1981) and David Scott, who was the commander.
Alan Bean, born Alan LaVern Bean was a crew member aboard NASA's Apollo 12. He retired in 1981. David Scott commanded Apollo 12 and Alfred Worden was the backup pilot.
